<p>This morning at 12:00am the main disk that holds our final master raid slice started to corrupt, this lasted for about 3 hours until the server was full of cores, at which point it completed failed. Due to this, serv1.isaw.nyu.edu is going into permanent shutdown. The last fsck worked and the server started, but in an effort to save our data and prevent anymore corruption the machine needs to stay down. There is nothing we can currently do except wait. If the drives arrive today, i'll attempt at repair otherwise it will not be until next week.</p>
